==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: gasmask
<hw>gasmask</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a mask with a filter which protects
the face and lungs against poisonous gases. It is used in warfare, and
also by police to allow them to effectively use tear gas or other
disabling gas to disperse a crowd or force fugitives to leave a
building.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> respirator, gas helmet.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gaslight</ent>⟦br⟧
